{"title": "Make Games, Not War", "content": "Some sort of competitive sport or game is used in lieu of warfare, in order to settle disputes with less bloodshed. Most examples of this trope DO usually end up being Blood Sports - less bloodshed doesn't mean no bloodshed, after all. Note, however, that not all examples of this trope are Blood Sports, and not all Blood Sports exemplify this trope, so it is not simply a sub-trope.\n\nSometimes, the protagonist-slash-game-player is one of the people in the dispute, but far more often, the protagonist is merely a pawn, being forced to play games on someone else's behalf.\n\nCompare Duels Decide Everything, where those involved can't even imagine a way of conflict resolution that doesn't involve the game. See also War Has Never Been So Much Fun.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MakeGamesNotWar", "media_links": ["https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MobileFighterGGundam", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/KinosJourney", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/StarshipGirlYamamotoYohko", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DogDays", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/GirlsUndPanzer", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/NoGameNoLife", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Rollerball", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FutureSport", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RobotJox", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ApprenticeAdept", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheMalloreon", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MythAdventures", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheAvatarChronicles", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BernardWerber", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LifeTheUniverseAndEverything", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TimeWars", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/HerculesTheLege